=== BOUNDARY RANK RECURSION ===
R_d = alternating sum of Omega: R_{d+1} = Omega_d - R_d for acyclic degrees

P_7 (m=3): R from bottom = [0, 0, 3, 3]
  R from top (d=5...7): [3, 3, 0]
  R_m = 3
  R_{m+2} = 3
  O_m - R_m = 6 (= R_{m+1} + β_m)
  O_{m+1} - R_{m+2} = 6 (= R_{m+1} + β_{m+1})
  6 == 6? YES ✓
  β_m = m(m-3)/2 = 0
  R_{m+1} = 6 - 0 = 6

P_11 (m=5): R from bottom = [0, 0, 5, 15, 55, 150]
  R from top (d=7...11): [390, 300, 150, 30, 0]
  R_m = 150
  R_{m+2} = 390
  O_m - R_m = 310 (= R_{m+1} + β_m)
  O_{m+1} - R_{m+2} = 310 (= R_{m+1} + β_{m+1})
  310 == 310? YES ✓
  β_m = m(m-3)/2 = 5
  R_{m+1} = 310 - 5 = 305

=== GENERATING FUNCTION ANALYSIS ===
Omega(x) = sum Omega_d * x^d

